Enable rpmforge
http://www.tecmint.com/enable-rpmforge-repository/

Enable epel
http://www.tecmint.com/how-to-enable-epel-repository-for-rhel-centos-6-5/

wget http://pkgs.repoforge.org/rpmforge-release/rpmforge-release-0.5.3-1.el7.rf.x86_64.rpm
sudo rpm -Uvh rpmforge-release-0.5.3-1.el7.rf.x86_64.rpm

Mint themes: (install mint-x icon rpm )
http://rpm.pbone.net/index.php3/stat/4/idpl/32989802/dir/opensuse/com/mint-x-icon-theme-1.3.1-1.1.noarch.rpm.html

NTFS
http://wiki.centos.org/TipsAndTricks/NTFS
yum install fuse fuse-ntfs-3g 

List windows 7
cp /boot/grub2/grub.cfg /boot/grub2/grub.cfg.bk
grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg

Install chrome:
Follow steps here:
http://www.tecmint.com/install-google-chrome-on-redhat-centos-fedora-linux/

Was giving the issue:
yum "Metadata file does not match checksum" problem

Resolution:

gedit /etc/yum.conf
then add the line
http_caching=packages

install Mate:
Enable epel http://linuxg.net/how-to-install-mate-1-8-on-centos-7-debian-jessie-and-debian-wheezy/
Follow: http://www.server-world.info/en/note?os=CentOS_7&p=x&f=7

sudo rpm -Uvh http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/7/x86_64/e/epel-release-7-5.noarch.rpm
sudo yum install epel-release-7-5.noarch.rpm
sudo yum -y groups install "Server with GUI" 
sudo yum --enablerepo=epel -y groups install "MATE Desktop" 

To list windows
sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /etc/grub2.cfg

Open JDK
yum install java-1.7.0-openjdk java-1.7.0-openjdk-devel

